  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Regulatory requirement 21 CFR 870.4360 governs the device class; an inline Requirement node capturing this obligation is embedded in the evidence package. The top-level profile binding for that requirement node is intentionally absent per W-SI-02 test conditions.",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou1-hemolysis-acceptability",
